He has released four studio albums: 1994's George Ducas, 1997's Where I Stand, 2013's 4340  and 2019's Yellow Rose Motel.

His first two albums charted six consecutive singles on the Billboard Hot Country Singles & Tracks (now Hot Country Songs) chart, the highest being his signature hit "Lipstick Promises" which reached No. 9  and was also a No. 1 CMT video.
Ducas was born in Galveston, Texas and was raised in his early years by his father Steve (an Exxon chemical engineer) and his mother Irene (a teacher and a poet) in nearby Texas City, Texas.
and he spent the next five years in California with his mother, who gave him his first guitar.
After working six months at an Atlanta bank, he quit and relocated to Nashville to pursue a full-time career in music.
Upon his move to Music City, Ducas performed in Nashville area clubs by night and honed his songwriting skills by day.
Later that year, Ducas signed a record deal with Liberty Records.
